meta {
  name: GET widget vehicle-status (lightweight glance card)
  type: http
  seq: 25
}

get {
  url: {{base_url}}/api/v2/widgets/vehicle-status/{{vin}}
  body: none
  auth: bearer
}

auth:bearer {
  token: {{access_token}}
}

headers {
  Accept: application/json
}

docs {
  v1.20.0 (Bundle 2 Phase A) — Skoda lightweight widget endpoint.
  Source: skodaconnect/myskoda PR #557 (merged 2026-04-15).

  Returns curated subset for in-app glance card:
    - vehicle.{name, licensePlate, renderUrl}
    - vehicleStatus.{doorsLocked, drivingRangeInKm}
    - chargingStatus.{stateOfChargeInPercent,
        remainingTimeToFullyChargedInMinutes}  // EV/PHEV only
    - parkingPosition.{state, maps.lightMapUrl, gpsCoordinates,
        formattedAddress}

  Use case: per-tick polling complement to /v2/vehicle-status/{vin}.
  Smaller payload than full vehicle-status; subscription tier: base.

  Implementation: SkodaClient.get_widget() in cariad/api/skoda.py.
  Wired into get_status() asyncio.gather as 9th endpoint.
  EXPECTED_KEYS["skoda"]["widget"] for Vehicle Data Scout coverage.
}
